This paper deals with the task of ranking online consumer reviews, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and data mining techniques. The paper focuses on predicting the helpfulness score of reviews using features extracted from review text, product description, and customer question-answer data. This task falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the organization, representation, storage, retrieval, and evaluation of information. The paper also involves the use of text classification and regression models, which are common in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the analysis of large-scale data, which is relevant to the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
